<seg id="125">2.</seg>
<seg id="126">In the Czech Republic, the variety of bridge structures built is greater than in Germany.</seg>
<seg id="127">In this context, the NKÚ noted that the construction of bridges is defined long before construction begins,</seg>
<seg id="128">already when the RMD submits the application for planning.</seg>
<seg id="129">At this point in time, it selects a specific bridge construction variant from several alternatives. However, profitability plays a minor role in this decision.</seg>
<seg id="130">Only by a thorough analysis of the construction sectors of both countries would a definitive conclusion have been possible with regard to bridge prices in the Czech Republic and Germany. However, this would have blown up the scope of this examination.</seg>
<seg id="131">The boundary bridge is the most expensive steel composite bridge on D 8 and A 17.</seg>
<seg id="132">The prices for the tunnels on the D 8 are about twice as high as in Germany.</seg>
<seg id="133">However, a comparison of the technical parameters between the tunnels on the D 8 and the tunnels in Germany showed no significant difference.</seg>
<seg id="134">The significant price differences may be the result of too low a level of competition for tunnel construction in the Czech Republic.</seg>
<seg id="135">However, the small number of tunnels did not allow generalizing conclusions.</seg>
<seg id="136">Efficiency and efficiency of the Dresden motorway - Prague</seg>
<seg id="137">The independent Czech Republic was founded in 1993.</seg>
<seg id="138">In the same year, the government adopted the plan for the expansion of the motorway network.</seg>
<seg id="139">The plan was to gradually expand the D 8 from Prague to the state border in Germany.</seg>
<seg id="140">The route section 0805 through the Bohemian Central Mountains should be built in front of the border section 0807.</seg>
<seg id="141">The Czech Republic finances D 8 under programme financing.</seg>
<seg id="142">The programme number 327 220 "Construction of the D 8 Prague motorway - Ústí nad Labem - Czech German state border" defines two objectives:</seg>
<seg id="143">1.</seg>
<seg id="144">as a national objective: to improve the link between Prague and Ústi nad Labem;</seg>
<seg id="145">2.</seg>
<seg id="146">as an international destination: the connection between Prague and Berlin as part of the Pan-European Transport Corridor IV BerlinIstanbul.</seg>
